'''This program takes an input from the user. The computer generates another random number using the 'random' module. If the user-input number and the computer generated 
number are same, the screen will display a message saying you have guessed the number right, otherwise not. For this, an if-else statement is used.
We are using 'random.randrange()' function. It is similar to the range() function.
Syntax:
random.randrange(start, stop, step)
Here:
start - integer specifying at which position to start. Default=0 (included) (optional)
stop - integer specifying at which position to end. (excluded) (required)
step - integer specifying the incrementation. Default=1 (optional) '''

#__main__
import random
num=(int(input("Enter any number between 1 and 10: ")))
x=random.randrange(1,10)
print("The system generated number is: ",x)
if x==num:
    print("Yayy!!! You guessed it right!")
else:
    print("Oopsies, wrong guess! Try again?")
